                   (GF-RNN), extends the existing approach of stacking multiple
                   recurrent layers by allowing and controlling signals flowing
                   from upper recurrent layers to lower layers using a global
                   gating unit for each pair of layers. The recurrent signals
                   exchanged between layers are gated adaptively based on the
