                   proposed modification (i) decouples the optimal choice of
                   weight decay factor from the setting of the learning rate
                   for both standard SGD and Adam and (ii) substantially
                   improves Adam's generalization performance, allowing it to
                   compete with SGD with momentum on image classification
                   datasets (on which it was previously typically outperformed
                   by the latter). Our proposed decoupled weight decay has
                   already been adopted by many researchers, and the community
                   has implemented it in TensorFlow and PyTorch; the complete
                   source code for our experiments is available at
