                   biomedical semantic segmentation, however, no specific
                   validations on GN were given. Most DCNNs for biomedical
                   semantic segmentation adopt BN as the normalization method
                   by default, without reviewing its performance. In this
                   paper, four normalization methods - BN, IN, LN and GN are
                   compared in details, specifically for 2D biomedical semantic
                   segmentation. U-Net is adopted as the basic DCNN structure.
                   Three datasets regarding the Right Ventricle (RV), aorta,
                   and Left Ventricle (LV) are used for the validation. The
                   results show that detailed subdivision of the feature map,
