  author   = "Keemink, Sander W and van Rossum, Mark C W",
  abstract = "As expressed in the Gestalt law of good continuation, human
              perception tends to associate stimuli that form smooth
              continuations. Contextual modulation in primary visual cortex, in
              the form of association fields, is believed to play an important
              role in this process. Yet a unified and principled account of the
              good continuation law on the neural level is lacking. In this
