              Shapley, Robert M and Hawken, Michael J",
  abstract = "Neurons in primary visual cortex, V1, very often have
              extraclassical receptive fields (eCRFs). The eCRF is defined as
              the region of visual space where stimuli cannot elicit a spiking
              response but can modulate the response of a stimulus in the
              classical receptive field (CRF). We investigated the dependence
              of the eCRF on stimulus contrast and orientation in macaque V1
              cells for which the laminar location was determined. The eCRF was
