              Laminar analysis revealed that the predominant bias for collinear
              suppression was found in layers 2/3 and 4b. The laminar pattern
              of contrast and orientation dependence suggests that eCRF
              suppression may derive from different neural circuits in
              different layers, and may be comprised of two distinct
