  author   = "Mumford, D",
  abstract = "This paper proposes that each area of the cortex carries on its
              calculations with the active participation of a nucleus in the
              thalamus with which it is reciprocally and topographically
              connected. Each cortical area is responsible for maintaining and
              updating the organism's knowledge of a specific aspect of the
              world, ranging from low level raw data to high level abstract
