              variable. We proposed that this aspect of DNA mutation testing
              could be standardized by developing a computer algorithm capable
              of accurately determining the percentage of malignant nuclei in
              an image of a hematoxylin and eosin-stained tissue. Using inForm
              software, we developed an algorithm, to calculate the percentage
              of malignant cells in histologic specimens of colon
              adenocarcinoma. A criterion standard was established by manually
              counting malignant and benign nuclei. Three pathologists also
              estimated the percentage of malignant nuclei in each image.
              Algorithm \#9 had a median deviation from the criterion standard
              of 5.4\% on the training set and 6.2\% on the validation set.
              Compared with pathologist estimation, Algorithm \#9 showed a
              similar ability to determine percentage of malignant nuclei. This
