  abstract = "A state-of-the-art attention network is extended and it is
              demonstrated that adding ClickMe supervision significantly
              improves its accuracy and yields visual features that are more
              interpretable and more similar to those used by human observers.
              Most recent gains in visual recognition have originated from the
              inclusion of attention mechanisms in deep convolutional networks
              (DCNs). Because these networks are optimized for object
              recognition, they learn where to attend using only a weak form of
