              experiment (ClickMe) used to supplement ImageNet with nearly half
              a million human-derived ``top-down'' attention maps. Using human
              psychophysics, we confirm that the identified top-down features
              from ClickMe are more diagnostic than ``bottom-up'' saliency
              features for rapid image categorization. As a proof of concept,
