  abstract      = "Designing convolutional neural networks (CNN) for mobile
                   devices is challenging because mobile models need to be
                   small and fast, yet still accurate. Although significant
                   efforts have been dedicated to design and improve mobile
                   CNNs on all dimensions, it is very difficult to manually
                   balance these trade-offs when there are so many
                   architectural possibilities to consider. In this paper, we
                   propose an automated mobile neural architecture search
                   (MNAS) approach, which explicitly incorporate model latency
                   into the main objective so that the search can identify a
                   model that achieves a good trade-off between accuracy and
