                   important gains to standard architectures for image, video
                   and fine-grained classification. For instance, by leveraging
                   one billion unlabelled images, our learned vanilla ResNet-50
                   achieves 81.2\% top-1 accuracy on the ImageNet benchmark.",
  month         =  may,
  year          =  2019,
  archivePrefix = "arXiv",
  primaryClass  = "cs.CV",
  eprint        = "1905.00546"
}

@ARTICLE{Zhang2020-my,
  title         = "{ResNeSt}: {Split-Attention} Networks",
  author        = "Zhang, Hang and Wu, Chongruo and Zhang, Zhongyue and Zhu, Yi
                   and Lin, Haibin and Zhang, Zhi and Sun, Yue and He, Tong and
                   Mueller, Jonas and Manmatha, R and Li, Mu and Smola,
                   Alexander",
  abstract      = "It is well known that featuremap attention and multi-path
                   representation are important for visual recognition. In this
                   paper, we present a modularized architecture, which applies
                   the channel-wise attention on different network branches to
